        <body>
            <div>
                <head>Translated parts</head>
                <p xml:id="CH1a0936-start">
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-1a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:12:20.227+09:00">In the seventh year of Emperor Gaozu of Han</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-1a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:12:39.237+09:00">Prime Minister Xiao He had the Weiyang Palace built.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:12:51.856+09:00">The main building was built on the side of the Dragonhead Mountain,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-1a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:13:07.878+09:00">and the palace gate towers stood to the north.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-1a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:13:45.479+09:00">The perimeter of Weiyang Place was in all 22 li, 90 bu, five chi (more than 9000 me].</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-1a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:14:05.363+09:00">The streets within had a togtal length of 70 li [29 km].</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-1a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:14:23.334+09:00">There were 43 halls built upon terraces:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-1a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:14:28.928+09:00">32 in th outer palce</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-1a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:14:50.585+09:00">eleven  in the inner palace.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-1a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:15:08.249+09:00">In the palace there were thriteen bodies of water</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-1a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:15:15.481+09:00">and six hills,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-1a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:15:28.669+09:00">including one lake and one hill in the rear part of the palace.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-1a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:15:50.718+09:00">There were 95 small gtes in total.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-2a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:16:19.558+09:00">The Wu Emperor had the Kunming Lake made.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-2a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:16:35.332+09:00">He wanted to attack the Kunwu Yi [barbarians],</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-2a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:16:59.963+09:00">and to teach and practice naval warfare.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-2a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:17:14.858+09:00">The late was also used for entertainment for the emperor and to raise fish.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-2a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:17:34.457+09:00">The fish were given to the ancestrsal temples for sacrifices,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-2a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:17:50.651+09:00">and any remaining were sold at the Chag'an market.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-2a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:18:09.107+09:00">The lake measured forty li around.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-2a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:18:29.736+09:00">In the Han system,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-2a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:19:32.891+09:00">in the eigth monthstrong wine was offered in the ancestral temple.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-2a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:20:16.167+09:00">They used wine fermented nine times, with the sacrificial animals.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-2a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:20:55.98+09:00">The emperor officiated.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-2a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:21:06.365+09:00">They made the wine at dawn on the first day of the year;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-2a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:21:36.564+09:00">it was ready in the eighth month.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-2a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:21:50.021+09:00">It was called strong wine,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-2a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:23:09.833+09:00">or "nine-fermented,"</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-2a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:23:33.666+09:00">or "full-bodied wine".</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-3a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:25:08.561+09:00">When therre was flooding in the capital</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-3a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:25:23.898+09:00">they sacrificed to the nountains and rivers to stop the rain.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-3a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:26:29.541+09:00">The prime minister and censors,and officials who received 2000 bushels of grain as salary, all prayed for the spirits to intervene.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-3a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:26:51.201+09:00">It was the same for pryers to ask for rain.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-3a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:30:11.781+09:00">The Son of Heaven's brushes</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-3a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:30:46.838+09:00">had handles inlaid with gems,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-3a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:31:39.376+09:00">and the bristles were all from the hair of autumn hares</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-3a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:33:21.808+09:00">The official Lu Hu made them.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-3a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:35:28.807+09:00">Their cases were made of various precious materials,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-3a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:35:51.794+09:00">with sides decorated with jade bi and kingfisher feathers,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-3a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:36:08.65+09:00">altogether worth a fortune.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-4a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:36:35.599+09:00">Under the Han system,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-4a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:38:44.909+09:00">the emperor's low table was jade.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-4a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:40:33.123+09:00">In the winter a thick brocade caled "table-silk" was laid on top.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-4a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:40:44.416+09:00">[table silk]</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-4a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:41:11.648+09:00">Elephant ivory was used for small braziers</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-4a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:44:10.762+09:00">which were decorated with flower patterns.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-4a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:45:52.126+09:00">In the rear palace, there were also five-colloured decorated satins.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-4a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:46:14.412+09:00">They used wine to grind ink</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-4a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:51:53.431+09:00">and jade inkstones</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-4a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:52:05.593+09:00">because these did not freeze.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-4a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:53:20.653+09:00">In the summer, feather fans were set out.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-4a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:54:04.155+09:00">The great nobles all used bamboo and wood for their low tables,  and in the winter</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-4a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:54:26.241+09:00">[The great nobles all used bamboo and wood for their low tables,]</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-4a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:54:56.477+09:00">and in the winter these were also covered with fine felt for them to lean on.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-4a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:55:21.809+09:00">They were not allowed to use silk brocade.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-5a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:56:05.499+09:00">In the time of Emperor Wu,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-5a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:57:27.844+09:00">a western domain presented him with a jiguang [a mythical beast, "lucky shining"] fur garment,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-5a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:57:40.484+09:00">which could go into water without getting wet.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-5a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T00:58:23.223+09:00">The emperor often wore this garment when he held court.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-5a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T01:11:25.014+09:00">The Emperor Gaozu's concubine, Lady Qi, played the zither and the lute very well.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-5a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T01:11:55.112+09:00">The em;peror often embraced Lady Qi, singing along to the strings.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-5a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T01:12:13.482+09:00">When the music finished,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-5a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T01:12:31.614+09:00">they would both be sobbing and tearful.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-5a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T01:13:17.889+09:00">Lady Qi also danced very well, waving her sleeves and bending her waist.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-5a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T01:13:56.981+09:00">She would sing the songs "Beyond the frontier," "Coming across the frontier," and "Hoping to go home;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-5a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T01:14:19.749+09:00">the hundreds of serving women would all practice these.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-5a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T01:14:33.036+09:00">In the rear palace, when they all sang together,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-5a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T01:15:28+09:00">the sound would reach the heavens.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-6a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T01:29:23.903+09:00">Lady Qi had rings made of god refined a hundred times,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-6a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T01:31:52.97+09:00">so bright you could see the bones of her fingers.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-6a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T01:33:48.101+09:00">The emperor did not like them</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-6a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T01:34:13.624+09:00">so she gave them to her servants mingyu, Yaoguang and others.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-6a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T01:34:39.4+09:00">They each got four rings.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-6a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T01:47:16.381+09:00">The Prince of Zhao, Ruyi [Lady Qi's son], was very young,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-6a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T01:39:05.622+09:00">and could not yet have a tutor from outside.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-6a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T01:39:51.39+09:00">Lady Qi had him taught by an old woman named Zhao, who had been the nurse of the King of the Zhao [Zhao Ao[.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-6a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T01:40:24.435+09:00">She called his building the "Raising-Virtue Palace,"</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH1a0936_CHANT_001-6a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-02-23T01:41:18.962+09:00">but later it was changed to "Fish and Water-Plant Palace".</seg>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
